Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @lamb steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lemon{1}(zested and cut into wedges).

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts) and a good squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with salt and pepper, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%sachet}.

> TIP: Lamb steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, ~{8-10%minutes} total. Turn every ~{2%minutes}.

> TIP: Cook each side for 1-2 min more if you like it more well done.

Once the lamb is cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{}, cover with @foil{}, and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The lamb is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Wipe out the (now empty) #frying pan{} and return to medium-high heat.

Add the @harissa paste{50%g}, @honey{15%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount). Stir together and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once thickened, stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted - this is your honey-harissa sauce.

Once the chips are cooked, crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} and sprinkle on the lemon zest. Toss to coat in the tray.

Just before everything's ready, add the baby gem to the #bowl{} of dressing and toss to coat.

Transfer the lamb steaks to your #plates{} and spoon over the honey-harissa sauce.

Serve the salad and Greek style chips alongside. Enjoy!